title: Diffraction analysis of elastic and inelastic scattering by magnesium.

x4freetext: Diffraction analysis of elastic and inelastic
scattering by magnesium.

x4codes.hlp: University of Washington, Seattle, WA, United States of America
University of Washington, Seattle, WA, United States of America

x4freetext: 152 cm cyclotron was used.
The incident beam energy was determined by
measuring range in aluminium with the aid of a double
proportional counter telescope.
The detection system for alpha particles
consisted of the single crystal CsI(Tl) detector. For
the deuteron runs a double CsI(Tl) counter was used
with the dE/dx and E crystal pulses in the desired
energy intervals simultaneously gating each other; the
desired energy intervals were obtained with single
channel differential pulse height analyzers. The
resolution for the alpha particle counter was typically
2% (with aluminium absorbers) of the full energy,
while that for the deuterons was typically 4% for the
E crystal.
The target material was 0.00076 cm commercial magnesium
foil.
The principal error in the elastic scattering
cross sections is due to the target density
measurement (3%); errors in the absolute inelastic
cross sections are generally larger because of
uncertainty in background subtraction.
The error in the angle of the detector
locating arms may be as large as 1 degree in certain
runs.
